  1713.     /**
  1714.      *    Wrap string values in quotes
  1715.      *
  1716.      *    @param mixed $value 
  1717.      *    @return mixed 
  1718.      */
  1719.     public static function _wrapResult($value) {
  1720.         if (is_string($value)) {
  1721.             //    Error values cannot be "wrapped"
  1722.             if (preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_ERROR.'$/i', $value, $match)) {
  1723.                 //    Return Excel errors "as is"
  1724.                 return $value;
  1725.             }
  1726.             //    Return strings wrapped in quotes
  1727.             return '"'.$value.'"';
  1728.         //    Convert numeric errors to NaN error
  1729.         } else if((is_float($value)) && ((is_nan($value)) || (is_infinite($value)))) {
  1730.             return PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::NaN();
  1731.         }
  1732.  
  1733.         return $value;
  1734.     }    //    function _wrapResult()
  1735.  
  1736.  
  1737.     /**
  1738.      *    Remove quotes used as a wrapper to identify string values
  1739.      *
  1740.      *    @param mixed $value 
  1741.      *    @return mixed 
  1742.      */
  1743.     public static function _unwrapResult($value) {
  1744.         if (is_string($value)) {
  1745.             if ((strlen($value) > 0) && ($value{0} == '"') && (substr($value,-1) == '"')) {
  1746.                 return substr($value,1,-1);
  1747.             }
  1748.         //    Convert numeric errors to NaN error
  1749.         } else if((is_float($value)) && ((is_nan($value)) || (is_infinite($value)))) {
  1750.             return PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::NaN();
  1751.         }
  1752.         return $value;
  1753.     }    //    function _unwrapResult()
  1754.  
  1755.  
  1756.  
  1757.  
  1758.     /**
  1759.      *    Calculate cell value (using formula from a cell ID)
  1760.      *    Retained for backward compatibility
  1761.      *
  1762.      *    @access    public
  1763.      *    @param    PHPExcel_Cell    $pCell    Cell to calculate
  1764.      *    @return    mixed 
  1765.      *    @throws    Exception
  1766.      */
  1767.     public function calculate(PHPExcel_Cell $pCell = null) {

  1769.     }    //    function calculate()
  1770.  
  1771.  
  1772.     /**
  1773.      *    Calculate the value of a cell formula
  1774.      *
  1775.      *    @access    public
  1776.      *    @param    PHPExcel_Cell    $pCell        Cell to calculate
  1777.      *    @param    Boolean            $resetLog    Flag indicating whether the debug log should be reset or not
  1778.      *    @return    mixed 
  1779.      *    @throws    Exception
  1780.      */
  1781.     public function calculateCellValue(PHPExcel_Cell $pCell = null, $resetLog = true) {
  1782.         if ($resetLog) {
  1783.             //    Initialise the logging settings if requested
  1784.             $this->formulaError = null;
  1785.             $this->debugLog = $this->debugLogStack = array();
  1786.  
  1787.             $returnArrayAsType = self::$returnArrayAsType;
  1788.             self::$returnArrayAsType = self::RETURN_ARRAY_AS_ARRAY;
  1789.         }
  1790.  
  1791.         //    Read the formula from the cell
  1792.         if (is_null($pCell)) {
  1793.             return null;
  1794.         }
  1795.  
  1796.         if ($resetLog) {
  1797.             self::$returnArrayAsType = $returnArrayAsType;
  1798.         }
  1799.         //    Execute the calculation for the cell formula
  1800.         $result = self::_unwrapResult($this->_calculateFormulaValue($pCell->getValue(), $pCell->getCoordinate(), $pCell));
  1801.  
  1802.         if ((is_array($result)) && (self::$returnArrayAsType != self::RETURN_ARRAY_AS_ARRAY)) {
  1803.             $testResult = PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::flattenArray($result);
  1804.             if (self::$returnArrayAsType == self::RETURN_ARRAY_AS_ERROR) {
  1805.                 return PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::VALUE();
  1806.             }
  1807.             //    If there's only a single cell in the array, then we allow it
  1808.             if (count($testResult) != 1) {
  1809.                 //    If keys are numeric, then it's a matrix result rather than a cell range result, so we permit it
  1810.                 $r = array_shift(array_keys($result));
  1811.                 if (!is_numeric($r)) { return PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::VALUE(); }
  1812.                 if (is_array($result[$r])) {
  1813.                     $c = array_shift(array_keys($result[$r]));
  1814.                     if (!is_numeric($c)) {
  1815.                         return PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::VALUE();
  1816.                     }
  1817.                 }
  1818.             }
  1819.             $result = array_shift($testResult);
  1820.         }
  1821.  
  1822.         if (is_null($result)) {
  1823.             return 0;
  1824.         } elseif((is_float($result)) && ((is_nan($result)) || (is_infinite($result)))) {
  1825.             return PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::NaN();
  1826.         }
  1827.         return $result;
  1828.     }    //    function calculateCellValue(
  1829.  
  1830.  
  1831.     /**
  1832.      *    Validate and parse a formula string
  1833.      *
  1834.      *    @param    string        $formula        Formula to parse
  1835.      *    @return    array 
  1836.      *    @throws    Exception
  1837.      */
  1838.     public function parseFormula($formula) {
  1839.         //    Basic validation that this is indeed a formula
  1840.         //    We return an empty array if not
  1841.         $formula = trim($formula);
  1842.         if ($formula{0} != '=') return array();
  1843.         $formula = trim(substr($formula,1));
  1844.         $formulaLength = strlen($formula);
  1845.         if ($formulaLength < 1) return array();
  1846.  
  1847.         //    Parse the formula and return the token stack
  1848.         return $this->_parseFormula($formula);
  1849.     }    //    function parseFormula()

  1852.     /**
  1853.      *    Calculate the value of a formula
  1854.      *
  1855.      *    @param    string        $formula        Formula to parse
  1856.      *    @return    mixed 
  1857.      *    @throws    Exception
  1858.      */
  1859.     public function calculateFormula($formula, $cellID=null, PHPExcel_Cell $pCell = null) {
  1860.         //    Initialise the logging settings
  1861.         $this->formulaError = null;
  1862.         $this->debugLog = $this->debugLogStack = array();
  1863.  
  1864.         //    Disable calculation cacheing because it only applies to cell calculations, not straight formulae
  1865.         //    But don't actually flush any cache
  1866.         $resetCache = $this->getCalculationCacheEnabled();
  1867.         $this->_calculationCacheEnabled = false;
  1868.         //    Execute the calculation
  1869.         $result = self::_unwrapResult($this->_calculateFormulaValue($formula, $cellID, $pCell));
  1870.         //    Reset calculation cacheing to its previous state
  1871.         $this->_calculationCacheEnabled = $resetCache;
  1872.  
  1873.         return $result;
  1874.     }    //    function calculateFormula()

  1877.     /**
  1878.      *    Parse a cell formula and calculate its value
  1879.      *
  1880.      *    @param    string            $formula    The formula to parse and calculate
  1881.      *    @param    string            $cellID        The ID (e.g. A3) of the cell that we are calculating
  1882.      *    @param    PHPExcel_Cell    $pCell        Cell to calculate
  1883.      *    @return    mixed 
  1884.      *    @throws    Exception
  1885.      */
  1886.     public function _calculateFormulaValue($formula, $cellID=null, PHPExcel_Cell $pCell = null) {
  1887. //        echo '<b>'.$cellID.'</b><br />';
  1888.         $cellValue = '';
  1889.  
  1890.         //    Basic validation that this is indeed a formula
  1891.         //    We simply return the "cell value" (formula) if not
  1892.         $formula = trim($formula);
  1893.         if ($formula{0} != '=') return self::_wrapResult($formula);
  1894.         $formula = trim(substr($formula,1));
  1895.         $formulaLength = strlen($formula);
  1896.         if ($formulaLength < 1) return self::_wrapResult($formula);
  1897.  
  1898.         $wsTitle = 'Wrk';
  1899.         if (!is_null($pCell)) {
  1900.             $wsTitle = urlencode($pCell->getParent()->getTitle());
  1901.         }
  1902.         // Is calculation cacheing enabled?
  1903.         if (!is_null($cellID)) {
  1904.             if ($this->_calculationCacheEnabled) {
  1905.                 // Is the value present in calculation cache?
  1906. //                echo 'Testing cache value<br />';
  1907.                 if (isset($this->_calculationCache[$wsTitle][$cellID])) {
  1908. //                    echo 'Value is in cache<br />';
  1909.                     $this->_writeDebug('Testing cache value for cell '.$cellID);
  1910.                     //    Is cache still valid?
  1911.                     if ((time() + microtime(true)) - $this->_calculationCache[$wsTitle][$cellID]['time'] < $this->_calculationCacheExpirationTime) {
  1912. //                        echo 'Cache time is still valid<br />';
  1913.                         $this->_writeDebug('Retrieving value for '.$cellID.' from cache');
  1914.                         // Return the cached result
  1915.                         $returnValue = $this->_calculationCache[$wsTitle][$cellID]['data'];
  1916. //                        echo 'Retrieving data value of '.$returnValue.' for '.$cellID.' from cache<br />';
  1917.                         if (is_array($returnValue)) {
  1918.                             return array_shift(PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::flattenArray($returnValue));
  1919.                         }
  1920.                         return $returnValue;
  1921.                     } else {
  1922. //                        echo 'Cache has expired<br />';
  1923.                         $this->_writeDebug('Cache value for '.$cellID.' has expired');
  1924.                         //    Clear the cache if it's no longer valid
  1925.                         unset($this->_calculationCache[$wsTitle][$cellID]);
  1926.                     }
  1927.                 }
  1928.             }
  1929.         }
  1930.  
  1931.         $this->debugLogStack[] = $cellID;
  1932.         //    Parse the formula onto the token stack and calculate the value
  1933.         $cellValue = $this->_processTokenStack($this->_parseFormula($formula), $cellID, $pCell);
  1934.         array_pop($this->debugLogStack);
  1935.  
  1936.         // Save to calculation cache
  1937.         if (!is_null($cellID)) {
  1938.             if ($this->_calculationCacheEnabled) {
  1939.                 $this->_calculationCache[$wsTitle][$cellID]['time'] = (time() + microtime(true));
  1940.                 $this->_calculationCache[$wsTitle][$cellID]['data'] = $cellValue;
  1941.             }
  1942.         }
  1943.  
  1944.         //    Return the calculated value
  1945.         return $cellValue;
  1946.     }    //    function _calculateFormulaValue()

  1949.     /**
  1950.      *    Ensure that paired matrix operands are both matrices and of the same size
  1951.      *
  1952.      *    @param    mixed        &$operand1    First matrix operand
  1953.      *    @param    mixed        &$operand2    Second matrix operand
  1954.      *    @param    integer        $resize        Flag indicating whether the matrices should be resized to match
  1955.      *                                         and (if so), whether the smaller dimension should grow or the
  1956.      *                                         larger should shrink.
  1957.      *                                             0 = no resize
  1958.      *                                             1 = shrink to fit
  1959.      *                                             2 = extend to fit
  1960.      */
  1961.     private static function _checkMatrixOperands(&$operand1,&$operand2,$resize = 1) {
  1962.         //    Examine each of the two operands, and turn them into an array if they aren't one already
  1963.         //    Note that this function should only be called if one or both of the operand is already an array
  1964.         if (!is_array($operand1)) {
  1965.             list($matrixRows,$matrixColumns) = self::_getMatrixDimensions($operand2);
  1966.             $operand1 = array_fill(0,$matrixRows,array_fill(0,$matrixColumns,$operand1));
  1967.             $resize = 0;
  1968.         } elseif (!is_array($operand2)) {
  1969.             list($matrixRows,$matrixColumns) = self::_getMatrixDimensions($operand1);
  1970.             $operand2 = array_fill(0,$matrixRows,array_fill(0,$matrixColumns,$operand2));
  1971.             $resize = 0;
  1972.         }
  1973.  
  1974.         list($matrix1Rows,$matrix1Columns) = self::_getMatrixDimensions($operand1);
  1975.         list($matrix2Rows,$matrix2Columns) = self::_getMatrixDimensions($operand2);
  1976.         if (($matrix1Rows == $matrix2Columns) && ($matrix2Rows == $matrix1Columns)) {
  1977.             $resize = 1;
  1978.         }
  1979.  
  1980.         if ($resize == 2) {
  1981.             //    Given two matrices of (potentially) unequal size, convert the smaller in each dimension to match the larger
  1982.             self::_resizeMatricesExtend($operand1,$operand2);
  1983.         } elseif ($resize == 1) {
  1984.             //    Given two matrices of (potentially) unequal size, convert the larger in each dimension to match the smaller
  1985.             self::_resizeMatricesShrink($operand1,$operand2);
  1986.         }
  1987.     }    //    function _checkMatrixOperands()
  1988.

  1990.     /**
  1991.      *    Read the dimensions of a matrix, and re-index it with straight numeric keys starting from row 0, column 0
  1992.      *
  1993.      *    @param    mixed        &$matrix        matrix operand
  1994.      *    @return    array        An array comprising the number of rows, and number of columns
  1995.      */
  1996.     public static function _getMatrixDimensions(&$matrix) {
  1997.         $matrixRows = count($matrix);
  1998.         $matrixColumns = 0;
  1999.         foreach($matrix as $rowKey => $rowValue) {
  2000.             $colCount = count($rowValue);
  2001.             if ($colCount > $matrixColumns) {
  2002.                 $matrixColumns = $colCount;
  2003.             }
  2004.             $matrix[$rowKey] = array_values($rowValue);
  2005.         }
  2006.         $matrix = array_values($matrix);
  2007.         return array($matrixRows,$matrixColumns);
  2008.     }    //    function _getMatrixDimensions()

  2011.     /**
  2012.      *    Ensure that paired matrix operands are both matrices of the same size
  2013.      *
  2014.      *    @param    mixed        &$matrix1    First matrix operand
  2015.      *    @param    mixed        &$matrix2    Second matrix operand
  2016.      */
  2017.     private static function _resizeMatricesShrink(&$matrix1,&$matrix2) {
  2018.         list($matrix1Rows,$matrix1Columns) = self::_getMatrixDimensions($matrix1);
  2019.         list($matrix2Rows,$matrix2Columns) = self::_getMatrixDimensions($matrix2);
  2020.  
  2021.         if (($matrix2Columns < $matrix1Columns) || ($matrix2Rows < $matrix1Rows)) {
  2022.             if ($matrix2Columns < $matrix1Columns) {
  2023.                 for ($i = 0; $i < $matrix1Rows; ++$i) {
  2024.                     for ($j = $matrix2Columns; $j < $matrix1Columns; ++$j) {
  2025.                         unset($matrix1[$i][$j]);
  2026.                     }
  2027.                 }
  2028.             }
  2029.             if ($matrix2Rows < $matrix1Rows) {
  2030.                 for ($i = $matrix2Rows; $i < $matrix1Rows; ++$i) {
  2031.                     unset($matrix1[$i]);
  2032.                 }
  2033.             }
  2034.         }
  2035.  
  2036.         if (($matrix1Columns < $matrix2Columns) || ($matrix1Rows < $matrix2Rows)) {
  2037.             if ($matrix1Columns < $matrix2Columns) {
  2038.                 for ($i = 0; $i < $matrix2Rows; ++$i) {
  2039.                     for ($j = $matrix1Columns; $j < $matrix2Columns; ++$j) {
  2040.                         unset($matrix2[$i][$j]);
  2041.                     }
  2042.                 }
  2043.             }
  2044.             if ($matrix1Rows < $matrix2Rows) {
  2045.                 for ($i = $matrix1Rows; $i < $matrix2Rows; ++$i) {
  2046.                     unset($matrix2[$i]);
  2047.                 }
  2048.             }
  2049.         }
  2050.     }    //    function _resizeMatricesShrink()
  2051.  
  2052.  
  2053.     /**
  2054.      *    Ensure that paired matrix operands are both matrices of the same size
  2055.      *
  2056.      *    @param    mixed        &$matrix1    First matrix operand
  2057.      *    @param    mixed        &$matrix2    Second matrix operand
  2058.      */
  2059.     private static function _resizeMatricesExtend(&$matrix1,&$matrix2) {
  2060.         list($matrix1Rows,$matrix1Columns) = self::_getMatrixDimensions($matrix1);
  2061.         list($matrix2Rows,$matrix2Columns) = self::_getMatrixDimensions($matrix2);
  2062.  
  2063.         if (($matrix2Columns < $matrix1Columns) || ($matrix2Rows < $matrix1Rows)) {
  2064.             if ($matrix2Columns < $matrix1Columns) {
  2065.                 for ($i = 0; $i < $matrix2Rows; ++$i) {
  2066.                     $x = $matrix2[$i][$matrix2Columns-1];
  2067.                     for ($j = $matrix2Columns; $j < $matrix1Columns; ++$j) {
  2068.                         $matrix2[$i][$j] = $x;
  2069.                     }
  2070.                 }
  2071.             }
  2072.             if ($matrix2Rows < $matrix1Rows) {
  2073.                 $x = $matrix2[$matrix2Rows-1];
  2074.                 for ($i = 0; $i < $matrix1Rows; ++$i) {
  2075.                     $matrix2[$i] = $x;
  2076.                 }
  2077.             }
  2078.         }
  2079.  
  2080.         if (($matrix1Columns < $matrix2Columns) || ($matrix1Rows < $matrix2Rows)) {
  2081.             if ($matrix1Columns < $matrix2Columns) {
  2082.                 for ($i = 0; $i < $matrix1Rows; ++$i) {
  2083.                     $x = $matrix1[$i][$matrix1Columns-1];
  2084.                     for ($j = $matrix1Columns; $j < $matrix2Columns; ++$j) {
  2085.                         $matrix1[$i][$j] = $x;
  2086.                     }
  2087.                 }
  2088.             }
  2089.             if ($matrix1Rows < $matrix2Rows) {
  2090.                 $x = $matrix1[$matrix1Rows-1];
  2091.                 for ($i = 0; $i < $matrix2Rows; ++$i) {
  2092.                     $matrix1[$i] = $x;
  2093.                 }
  2094.             }
  2095.         }
  2096.     }    //    function _resizeMatricesExtend()

  2099.     /**
  2100.      *    Format details of an operand for display in the log (based on operand type)
  2101.      *
  2102.      *    @param    mixed        $value    First matrix operand

  2104.      */
  2105.     private static function _showValue($value) {
  2106.         if (is_array($value)) {

  2108.             $pad = $rpad = ', ';
  2109.             foreach($value as $row) {

  2111.                     $returnMatrix[] = implode($pad,$row);

  2113.                 } else {
  2114.                     $returnMatrix[] = $row;
  2115.                 }

  2117.             return '{ '.implode($rpad,$returnMatrix).' }';
  2118.         } elseif(is_bool($value)) {
  2119.             return ($value) ? 'TRUE' : 'FALSE';
  2120.         }
  2121.

  2123.     }    //    function _showValue()

  2126.     /**
  2127.      *    Format type and details of an operand for display in the log (based on operand type)

  2132.     private static function _showTypeDetails($value) {
  2133.         switch (gettype($value)) {
  2134.             case 'double'    :
  2135.             case 'float'    :
  2136.                 $typeString = 'a floating point number';
  2137.                 break;
  2138.             case 'integer'    :
  2139.                 $typeString = 'an integer number';
  2140.                 break;
  2141.             case 'boolean'    :
  2142.                 $typeString = 'a boolean';
  2143.                 break;
  2144.             case 'array'    :
  2145.                 $typeString = 'a matrix';
  2146.                 break;
  2147.             case 'string'    :
  2148.                 if ($value == '') {
  2149.                     return 'an empty string';
  2150.                 } elseif ($value{0} == '#') {
  2151.                     return 'a '.$value.' error';
  2152.                 } else {
  2153.                     $typeString = 'a string';
  2154.                 }
  2155.                 break;
  2156.             case 'NULL'    :
  2157.                 return 'a null value';
  2158.         }
  2159.         return $typeString.' with a value of '.self::_showValue($value);
  2160.     }    //    function _showTypeDetails()

  2163.     private static function _convertMatrixReferences($formula) {
  2164.         static $matrixReplaceFrom = array('{',';','}');
  2165.         static $matrixReplaceTo = array('MKMATRIX(MKMATRIX(','),MKMATRIX(','))');
  2166.  
  2167.         //    Convert any Excel matrix references to the MKMATRIX() function
  2168.         if (strpos($formula,'{') !== false) {
  2169.             //    If there is the possibility of braces within a quoted string, then we don't treat those as matrix indicators
  2170.             if (strpos($formula,'"') !== false) {
  2171.                 //    So instead we skip replacing in any quoted strings by only replacing in every other array element after we've exploded
  2172.                 //        the formula
  2173.                 $temp = explode('"',$formula);
  2174.                 //    Open and Closed counts used for trapping mismatched braces in the formula
  2175.                 $openCount = $closeCount = 0;
  2176.                 foreach($temp as $i => &$value) {
  2177.                     //    Only count/replace in alternate array entries
  2178.                     if (($i % 2) == 0) {
  2179.                         $openCount += substr_count($value,'{');
  2180.                         $closeCount += substr_count($value,'}');
  2181.                         $value = str_replace($matrixReplaceFrom,$matrixReplaceTo,$value);
  2182.                     }
  2183.                 }
  2184.                 unset($value);
  2185.                 //    Then rebuild the formula string
  2186.                 $formula = implode('"',$temp);
  2187.             } else {
  2188.                 //    If there's no quoted strings, then we do a simple count/replace
  2189.                 $openCount = substr_count($formula,'{');
  2190.                 $closeCount = substr_count($formula,'}');
  2191.                 $formula = str_replace($matrixReplaceFrom,$matrixReplaceTo,$formula);
  2192.             }
  2193.             //    Trap for mismatched braces and trigger an appropriate error
  2194.             if ($openCount < $closeCount) {
  2195.                 if ($openCount > 0) {
  2196.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Mismatched matrix braces '}'");
  2197.                 } else {
  2198.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Unexpected '}' encountered");
  2199.                 }
  2200.             } elseif ($openCount > $closeCount) {
  2201.                 if ($closeCount > 0) {
  2202.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Mismatched matrix braces '{'");
  2203.                 } else {
  2204.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Unexpected '{' encountered");
  2205.                 }
  2206.             }
  2207.         }
  2208.  
  2209.         return $formula;

  2218.     // Convert infix to postfix notation
  2219.     private function _parseFormula($formula) {
  2220.         if (($formula = self::_convertMatrixReferences(trim($formula))) === false) {
  2221.             return false;
  2222.         }
  2223.  
  2224.         //    Binary Operators
  2225.         //    These operators always work on two values
  2226.         //    Array key is the operator, the value indicates whether this is a left or right associative operator
  2227.         $operatorAssociativity    = array('^' => 0,                                                            //    Exponentiation
  2228.                                         '*' => 0, '/' => 0,                                                 //    Multiplication and Division
  2229.                                         '+' => 0, '-' => 0,                                                    //    Addition and Subtraction
  2230.                                         '&' => 0,                                                            //    Concatenation
  2231.                                         '|' => 0, ':' => 0,                                                    //    Intersect and Range
  2232.                                         '>' => 0, '<' => 0, '=' => 0, '>=' => 0, '<=' => 0, '<>' => 0        //    Comparison
  2233.                                        );
  2234.         //    Comparison (Boolean) Operators
  2235.         //    These operators work on two values, but always return a boolean result
  2236.         $comparisonOperators    = array('>', '<', '=', '>=', '<=', '<>');
  2237.  
  2238.         //    Operator Precedence

  2241.         $operatorPrecedence    = array(':' => 8,                                                                //    Range
  2242.                                     '|' => 7,                                                                //    Intersect
  2243.                                     '~' => 6,                                                                //    Negation
  2244.                                     '%' => 5,                                                                //    Percentage
  2245.                                     '^' => 4,                                                                //    Exponentiation
  2246.                                     '*' => 3, '/' => 3,                                                     //    Multiplication and Division
  2247.                                     '+' => 2, '-' => 2,                                                        //    Addition and Subtraction
  2248.                                     '&' => 1,                                                                //    Concatenation
  2249.                                     '>' => 0, '<' => 0, '=' => 0, '>=' => 0, '<=' => 0, '<>' => 0            //    Comparison
  2250.                                    );
  2251.  
  2252.         $regexpMatchString = '/^('.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_FUNCTION.
  2253.                                '|'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_NUMBER.
  2254.                                '|'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_STRING.
  2255.                                '|'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_OPENBRACE.
  2256.                                '|'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_CELLREF.
  2257.                                '|'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_NAMEDRANGE.
  2258.                                '|'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_ERROR.
  2259.                              ')/si';

  2261.         //    Start with initialisation
  2262.         $index = 0;
  2263.         $stack = new PHPExcel_Token_Stack;
  2264.         $output = array();
  2265.         $expectingOperator = false;                    //    We use this test in syntax-checking the expression to determine when a
  2266.                                                     //        - is a negation or + is a positive operator rather than an operation
  2267.         $expectingOperand = false;                    //    We use this test in syntax-checking the expression to determine whether an operand
  2268.                                                     //        should be null in a function call
  2269.         //    The guts of the lexical parser

  2271.         while(True) {
  2272. //            echo 'Assessing Expression <b>'.substr($formula, $index).'</b><br />';

  2278.             }

  2281.             $isOperandOrFunction = preg_match($regexpMatchString, substr($formula, $index), $match);
  2282. //            echo '$isOperandOrFunction is '.(($isOperandOrFunction)?'True':'False').'<br />';
  2283.  
  2284.             if ($opCharacter == '-' && !$expectingOperator) {                //    Is it a negation instead of a minus?
  2285. //                echo 'Element is a Negation operator<br />';
  2286.                 $stack->push('Unary Operator','~');                            //    Put a negation on the stack
  2287.                 ++$index;                                                    //        and drop the negation symbol
  2288.             } elseif ($opCharacter == '%' && $expectingOperator) {
  2289. //                echo 'Element is a Percentage operator<br />';
  2290.                 $stack->push('Unary Operator','%');                            //    Put a percentage on the stack
  2291.                 ++$index;
  2292.             } elseif ($opCharacter == '+' && !$expectingOperator) {            //    Positive (rather than plus) can be discarded?

  2295.             } elseif (($opCharacter == '~') && (!$isOperandOrFunction)) {                    //    We have to explicitly deny a tilde, because it's legal
  2296.                 return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Illegal character '~'");    //        on the stack but not in the input expression
  2297.  
  2298.             } elseif ((in_array($opCharacter, $this->_operators) or $isOperandOrFunction) && $expectingOperator) {    //    Are we putting an operator on the stack?
  2299. //                echo 'Element with value '.$opCharacter.' is an Operator<br />';
  2300.                 while($stack->count() > 0 &&
  2301.                     ($o2 = $stack->last()) &&
  2302.                     in_array($o2['value'], $this->_operators) &&
  2303.                     @($operatorAssociativity[$opCharacter] ? $operatorPrecedence[$opCharacter] < $operatorPrecedence[$o2['value']] : $operatorPrecedence[$opCharacter] <= $operatorPrecedence[$o2['value']])) {
  2304.                     $output[] = $stack->pop();                                //    Swap operands and higher precedence operators from the stack to the output
  2305.                 }
  2306.                 $stack->push('Binary Operator',$opCharacter);    //    Finally put our current operator onto the stack
  2307.                 ++$index;
  2308.                 $expectingOperator = false;
  2309.  
  2310.             } elseif ($opCharacter == ')' && $expectingOperator) {            //    Are we expecting to close a parenthesis?
  2311. //                echo 'Element is a Closing bracket<br />';
  2312.                 $expectingOperand = false;
  2313.                 while (($o2 = $stack->pop()) && $o2['value'] != '(') {        //    Pop off the stack back to the last (
  2314.                     if (is_null($o2)) return $this->_raiseFormulaError('Formula Error: Unexpected closing brace ")"');
  2315.                     else $output[] = $o2;
  2316.                 }
  2317.                 $d = $stack->last(2);
  2318.                 if (preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_FUNCTION.'$/i', $d['value'], $matches)) {    //    Did this parenthesis just close a function?
  2319.                     $functionName = $matches[1];                                        //    Get the function name
  2320. //                    echo 'Closed Function is '.$functionName.'<br />';
  2321.                     $d = $stack->pop();
  2322.                     $argumentCount = $d['value'];        //    See how many arguments there were (argument count is the next value stored on the stack)
  2323. //                    if ($argumentCount == 0) {
  2324. //                        echo 'With no arguments<br />';
  2325. //                    } elseif ($argumentCount == 1) {
  2326. //                        echo 'With 1 argument<br />';
  2327. //                    } else {
  2328. //                        echo 'With '.$argumentCount.' arguments<br />';
  2329. //                    }
  2330.                     $output[] = $d;                        //    Dump the argument count on the output
  2331.                     $output[] = $stack->pop();            //    Pop the function and push onto the output
  2332.                     if (array_key_exists($functionName, $this->_controlFunctions)) {
  2333. //                        echo 'Built-in function '.$functionName.'<br />';
  2334.                         $expectedArgumentCount = $this->_controlFunctions[$functionName]['argumentCount'];
  2335.                         $functionCall = $this->_controlFunctions[$functionName]['functionCall'];
  2336.                     } elseif (array_key_exists($functionName, $this->_PHPExcelFunctions)) {
  2337. //                        echo 'PHPExcel function '.$functionName.'<br />';
  2338.                         $expectedArgumentCount = $this->_PHPExcelFunctions[$functionName]['argumentCount'];
  2339.                         $functionCall = $this->_PHPExcelFunctions[$functionName]['functionCall'];
  2340.                     } else {    // did we somehow push a non-function on the stack? this should never happen
  2341.                         return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Internal error, non-function on stack");
  2342.                     }
  2343.                     //    Check the argument count
  2344.                     $argumentCountError = False;
  2345.                     if (is_numeric($expectedArgumentCount)) {
  2346.                         if ($expectedArgumentCount < 0) {

  2348.                             if ($argumentCount > abs($expectedArgumentCount)) {
  2349.                                 $argumentCountError = True;
  2350.                                 $expectedArgumentCountString = 'no more than '.abs($expectedArgumentCount);
  2351.                             }
  2352.                         } else {
  2353. //                            echo '$expectedArgumentCount is numeric '.$expectedArgumentCount.'<br />';
  2354.                             if ($argumentCount != $expectedArgumentCount) {
  2355.                                 $argumentCountError = True;
  2356.                                 $expectedArgumentCountString = $expectedArgumentCount;
  2357.                             }
  2358.                         }
  2359.                     } elseif ($expectedArgumentCount != '*') {
  2360.                         $isOperandOrFunction = preg_match('/(\d*)([-+,])(\d*)/',$expectedArgumentCount,$argMatch);

  2362. //                        echo '<br />';

  2365.                                 if ($argumentCount < $argMatch[1]) {
  2366.                                     $argumentCountError = True;
  2367.                                     $expectedArgumentCountString = $argMatch[1].' or more ';
  2368.                                 }

  2372.                                     $argumentCountError = True;
  2373.                                     $expectedArgumentCountString = 'between '.$argMatch[1].' and '.$argMatch[3];
  2374.                                 }
  2375.                                 break;
  2376.                             case ',' :
  2377.                                 if (($argumentCount != $argMatch[1]) && ($argumentCount != $argMatch[3])) {
  2378.                                     $argumentCountError = True;
  2379.                                     $expectedArgumentCountString = 'either '.$argMatch[1].' or '.$argMatch[3];
  2380.                                 }
  2381.                                 break;
  2382.                         }
  2383.                     }
  2384.                     if ($argumentCountError) {
  2385.                         return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Wrong number of arguments for $functionName() function: $argumentCount given, ".$expectedArgumentCountString." expected");
  2386.                     }
  2387.                 }
  2388.                 ++$index;
  2389.  
  2390.             } elseif ($opCharacter == ',') {            //    Is this the comma separator for function arguments?
  2391. //                echo 'Element is a Function argument separator<br />';
  2392.                 while (($o2 = $stack->pop()) && $o2['value'] != '(') {        //    Pop off the stack back to the last (
  2393.                     if (is_null($o2)) return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Unexpected ','");
  2394.                     else $output[] = $o2;    // pop the argument expression stuff and push onto the output
  2395.                 }
  2396.                 //    If we've a comma when we're expecting an operand, then what we actually have is a null operand;
  2397.                 //        so push a null onto the stack
  2398.                 if (($expectingOperand) || (!$expectingOperator)) {
  2399.                     $output[] = array('type' => 'NULL Value', 'value' => $this->_ExcelConstants['NULL'], 'reference' => NULL);
  2400.                 }

  2402.                 $d = $stack->last(2);
  2403.                 if (!preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_FUNCTION.'$/i', $d['value'], $matches))
  2404.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Unexpected ','");
  2405.                 $d = $stack->pop();
  2406.                 $stack->push($d['type'],++$d['value'],$d['reference']);    // increment the argument count

  2417.             } elseif ($isOperandOrFunction && !$expectingOperator) {    // do we now have a function/variable/number?
  2418.                 $expectingOperator = true;
  2419.                 $expectingOperand = false;
  2420.                 $val = $match[1];
  2421.                 $length = strlen($val);

  2438.                     } else {    // it's a var w/ implicit multiplication
  2439.                         $output[] = array('type' => 'Value', 'value' => $matches[1], 'reference' => NULL);
  2440.                     }
  2441.                 } elseif (preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_CELLREF.'$/i', $val, $matches)) {
  2442. //                    echo 'Element '.$val.' is a Cell reference<br />';
  2443. //                    Watch for this case-change when modifying to allow cell references in different worksheets...
  2444. //                        Should only be applied to the actual cell column, not the worksheet name
  2445.                     $cellRef = strtoupper($val);
  2446. //                    $output[] = $cellRef;
  2447.                     $output[] = array('type' => 'Cell Reference', 'value' => $val, 'reference' => $cellRef);

  2452. //                        echo 'Element is a String<br />';

  2454.                     } elseif (is_numeric($val)) {
  2455. //                        echo 'Element is a Number<br />';

  2459.                         } else {

  2461.                             $val = (integer) $val;

  2466.                         $val = $this->_ExcelConstants[$excelConstant];
  2467.                     }
  2468.                     $output[] = array('type' => 'Value', 'value' => $val, 'reference' => NULL);
  2469.                 }
  2470.                 $index += $length;
  2471.  
  2472.             } elseif ($opCharacter == ')') {    // miscellaneous error checking
  2473.                 if ($expectingOperand) {
  2474.                     $output[] = array('type' => 'Null Value', 'value' => $this->_ExcelConstants['NULL'], 'reference' => NULL);
  2475.                     $expectingOperand = false;
  2476.                     $expectingOperator = True;
  2477.                 } else {
  2478.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Unexpected ')'");
  2479.                 }
  2480.             } elseif (in_array($opCharacter, $this->_operators) && !$expectingOperator) {
  2481.                 return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Unexpected operator '$opCharacter'");
  2482.             } else {    // I don't even want to know what you did to get here
  2483.                 return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: An unexpected error occured");
  2484.             }
  2485.             //    Test for end of formula string
  2486.             if ($index == strlen($formula)) {
  2487.                 //    Did we end with an operator?.
  2488.                 //    Only valid for the % unary operator
  2489.                 if ((in_array($opCharacter, $this->_operators)) && ($opCharacter != '%')) {
  2490.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Operator '$opCharacter' has no operands");
  2491.                 } else {
  2492.                     break;
  2493.                 }
  2494.             }
  2495.             //    Ignore white space
  2496.             while (($formula{$index} == "\n") || ($formula{$index} == "\r")) {
  2497.                 ++$index;
  2498.             }
  2499.             if ($formula{$index} == ' ') {
  2500.                 while ($formula{$index} == ' ') {
  2501.                     ++$index;
  2502.                 }
  2503.                 //    If we're expecting an operator, but only have a space between the previous and next operands (and both are
  2504.                 //        Cell References) then we have an INTERSECTION operator
  2505. //                echo 'Possible Intersect Operator<br />';
  2506.                 if (($expectingOperator) && (preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_CELLREF.'.*/i', substr($formula, $index), $match)) &&
  2507.                     ($output[count($output)-1]['type'] == 'Cell Reference')) {
  2508. //                    echo 'Element is an Intersect Operator<br />';
  2509.                     while($stack->count() > 0 &&
  2510.                         ($o2 = $stack->last()) &&
  2511.                         in_array($o2['value'], $this->_operators) &&
  2512.                         @($operatorAssociativity[$opCharacter] ? $operatorPrecedence[$opCharacter] < $operatorPrecedence[$o2['value']] : $operatorPrecedence[$opCharacter] <= $operatorPrecedence[$o2['value']])) {
  2513.                         $output[] = $stack->pop();                                //    Swap operands and higher precedence operators from the stack to the output
  2514.                     }
  2515.                     $stack->push('Binary Operator','|');    //    Put an Intersect Operator on the stack
  2516.                     $expectingOperator = false;
  2517.                 }
  2518.             }
  2519.         }
  2520.  
  2521.         while (!is_null($op = $stack->pop())) {    // pop everything off the stack and push onto output
  2522.             if ($opCharacter['value'] == '(') return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Expecting ')'");    // if there are any opening braces on the stack, then braces were unbalanced
  2523.             $output[] = $op;
  2524.         }
  2525.         return $output;
  2526.     }    //    function _parseFormula()
  2527.  
  2528.  
  2529.     // evaluate postfix notation
  2530.     private function _processTokenStack($tokens, $cellID=null, PHPExcel_Cell $pCell = null) {
  2531.         if ($tokens == false) return false;
  2532.  
  2533.         $stack = new PHPExcel_Token_Stack;
  2534.  
  2535.         //    Loop through each token in turn
  2536.         foreach ($tokens as $tokenData) {
  2537. //            print_r($tokenData);
  2538. //            echo '<br />';
  2539.             $token = $tokenData['value'];
  2540. //            echo '<b>Token is '.$token.'</b><br />';
  2541.             // if the token is a binary operator, pop the top two values off the stack, do the operation, and push the result back on the stack
  2542.             if (in_array($token, $this->_binaryOperators, true)) {
  2543. //                echo 'Token is a binary operator<br />';
  2544.                 //    We must have two operands, error if we don't
  2545.                 if (is_null($operand2Data = $stack->pop())) return $this->_raiseFormulaError('Internal error - Operand value missing from stack');
  2546.                 if (is_null($operand1Data = $stack->pop())) return $this->_raiseFormulaError('Internal error - Operand value missing from stack');
  2547.                 //    Log what we're doing
  2548.                 $operand1 = $operand1Data['value'];
  2549.                 $operand2 = $operand2Data['value'];
  2550.                 if ($token == ':') {
  2551.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating Range '.self::_showValue($operand1Data['reference']).$token.self::_showValue($operand2Data['reference']));
  2552.                 } else {
  2553.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating '.self::_showValue($operand1).' '.$token.' '.self::_showValue($operand2));
  2554.                 }
  2555.                 //    Process the operation in the appropriate manner
  2556.                 switch ($token) {
  2557.                     //    Comparison (Boolean) Operators
  2558.                     case '>'    :            //    Greater than
  2559.                     case '<'    :            //    Less than
  2560.                     case '>='    :            //    Greater than or Equal to
  2561.                     case '<='    :            //    Less than or Equal to
  2562.                     case '='    :            //    Equality
  2563.                     case '<>'    :            //    Inequality
  2564.                         $this->_executeBinaryComparisonOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$token,$stack);
  2565.                         break;
  2566.                     //    Binary Operators
  2567.                     case ':'    :            //    Range
  2568.                         $sheet1 = $sheet2 = '';
  2569.                         if (strpos($operand1Data['reference'],'!') !== false) {
  2570.                             list($sheet1,$operand1Data['reference']) = explode('!',$operand1Data['reference']);
  2571.                         } else {
  2572.                             $sheet1 = $pCell->getParent()->getTitle();
  2573.                         }
  2574.                         if (strpos($operand2Data['reference'],'!') !== false) {
  2575.                             list($sheet2,$operand2Data['reference']) = explode('!',$operand2Data['reference']);
  2576.                         } else {
  2577.                             $sheet2 = $sheet1;
  2578.                         }
  2579.                         if ($sheet1 == $sheet2) {
  2580.                             if (is_null($operand1Data['reference'])) {
  2581.                                 if ((trim($operand1Data['value']) != '') && (is_numeric($operand1Data['value']))) {
  2582.                                     $operand1Data['reference'] = $pCell->getColumn().$operand1Data['value'];
  2583.                                 } elseif (trim($operand1Data['reference']) == '') {
  2584.                                     $operand1Data['reference'] = $pCell->getColumn().$pCell->getRow();
  2585.                                 } else {
  2586.                                     $operand1Data['reference'] = $operand1Data['value'].$pCell->getRow();
  2587.                                 }
  2588.                             }
  2589.                             if (is_null($operand2Data['reference'])) {
  2590.                                 if ((trim($operand2Data['value']) != '') && (is_numeric($operand2Data['value']))) {
  2591.                                     $operand2Data['reference'] = $pCell->getColumn().$operand2Data['value'];
  2592.                                 } elseif (trim($operand2Data['reference']) == '') {
  2593.                                     $operand2Data['reference'] = $pCell->getColumn().$pCell->getRow();
  2594.                                 } else {
  2595.                                     $operand2Data['reference'] = $operand2Data['value'].$pCell->getRow();
  2596.                                 }
  2597.                             }
  2598.  
  2599.                             $oData = array_merge(explode(':',$operand1Data['reference']),explode(':',$operand2Data['reference']));
  2600.                             $oCol = $oRow = array();
  2601.                             foreach($oData as $oDatum) {
  2602.                                 $oCR = PHPExcel_Cell::coordinateFromString($oDatum);
  2603.                                 $oCol[] = PHPExcel_Cell::columnIndexFromString($oCR[0]) - 1;
  2604.                                 $oRow[] = $oCR[1];
  2605.                             }
  2606.                             $cellRef = PHPExcel_Cell::stringFromColumnIndex(min($oCol)).min($oRow).':'.PHPExcel_Cell::stringFromColumnIndex(max($oCol)).max($oRow);
  2607.                             $cellValue = $this->extractCellRange($cellRef, $pCell->getParent()->getParent()->getSheetByName($sheet1), false);
  2608.                             $stack->push('Cell Reference',$cellValue,$cellRef);
  2609.                         } else {
  2610.                             $stack->push('Error',PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::REF(),NULL);
  2611.                         }
  2612.  
  2613.                         break;
  2614.                     case '+'    :            //    Addition
  2615.                         $this->_executeNumericBinaryOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$token,'plusEquals',$stack);
  2616.                         break;
  2617.                     case '-'    :            //    Subtraction
  2618.                         $this->_executeNumericBinaryOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$token,'minusEquals',$stack);
  2619.                         break;
  2620.                     case '*'    :            //    Multiplication
  2621.                         $this->_executeNumericBinaryOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$token,'arrayTimesEquals',$stack);
  2622.                         break;
  2623.                     case '/'    :            //    Division
  2624.                         $this->_executeNumericBinaryOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$token,'arrayRightDivide',$stack);
  2625.                         break;
  2626.                     case '^'    :            //    Exponential
  2627.                         $this->_executeNumericBinaryOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$token,'power',$stack);
  2628.                         break;
  2629.                     case '&'    :            //    Concatenation
  2630.                         //    If either of the operands is a matrix, we need to treat them both as matrices
  2631.                         //        (converting the other operand to a matrix if need be); then perform the required
  2632.                         //        matrix operation
  2633.                         if (is_bool($operand1)) {
  2634.                             $operand1 = ($operand1) ? 'TRUE' : 'FALSE';
  2635.                         }
  2636.                         if (is_bool($operand2)) {
  2637.                             $operand2 = ($operand2) ? 'TRUE' : 'FALSE';
  2638.                         }
  2639.                         if ((is_array($operand1)) || (is_array($operand2))) {
  2640.                             //    Ensure that both operands are arrays/matrices
  2641.                             self::_checkMatrixOperands($operand1,$operand2,2);
  2642.                             try {
  2643.                                 //    Convert operand 1 from a PHP array to a matrix
  2644.                                 $matrix = new Matrix($operand1);
  2645.                                 //    Perform the required operation against the operand 1 matrix, passing in operand 2
  2646.                                 $matrixResult = $matrix->concat($operand2);
  2647.                                 $result = $matrixResult->getArray();
  2648.                             } catch (Exception $ex) {
  2649.                                 $this->_writeDebug('JAMA Matrix Exception: '.$ex->getMessage());
  2650.                                 $result = '#VALUE!';
  2651.                             }
  2652.                         } else {
  2653.                             $result = '"'.str_replace('""','"',self::_unwrapResult($operand1,'"').self::_unwrapResult($operand2,'"')).'"';
  2654.                         }
  2655.                         $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is '.self::_showTypeDetails($result));
  2656.                         $stack->push('Value',$result);
  2657.                         break;
  2658.                     case '|'    :            //    Intersect
  2659.                         $rowIntersect = array_intersect_key($operand1,$operand2);
  2660.                         $cellIntersect = $oCol = $oRow = array();
  2661.                         foreach(array_keys($rowIntersect) as $col) {
  2662.                             $oCol[] = PHPExcel_Cell::columnIndexFromString($col) - 1;
  2663.                             $cellIntersect[$col] = array_intersect_key($operand1[$col],$operand2[$col]);
  2664.                             foreach($cellIntersect[$col] as $row => $data) {
  2665.                                 $oRow[] = $row;
  2666.                             }
  2667.                         }
  2668.                         $cellRef = PHPExcel_Cell::stringFromColumnIndex(min($oCol)).min($oRow).':'.PHPExcel_Cell::stringFromColumnIndex(max($oCol)).max($oRow);
  2669.                         $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is '.self::_showTypeDetails($cellIntersect));
  2670.                         $stack->push('Value',$cellIntersect,$cellRef);
  2671.                         break;
  2672.                 }
  2673.  
  2674.             // if the token is a unary operator, pop one value off the stack, do the operation, and push it back on
  2675.             } elseif (($token === '~') || ($token === '%')) {
  2676. //                echo 'Token is a unary operator<br />';
  2677.                 if (is_null($arg = $stack->pop())) return $this->_raiseFormulaError('Internal error - Operand value missing from stack');
  2678.                 $arg = $arg['value'];
  2679.                 if ($token === '~') {
  2680. //                    echo 'Token is a negation operator<br />';
  2681.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating Negation of '.self::_showValue($arg));
  2682.                     $multiplier = -1;
  2683.                 } else {
  2684. //                    echo 'Token is a percentile operator<br />';
  2685.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating Percentile of '.self::_showValue($arg));
  2686.                     $multiplier = 0.01;
  2687.                 }
  2688.                 if (is_array($arg)) {
  2689.                     self::_checkMatrixOperands($arg,$multiplier,2);
  2690.                     try {
  2691.                         $matrix1 = new Matrix($arg);
  2692.                         $matrixResult = $matrix1->arrayTimesEquals($multiplier);
  2693.                         $result = $matrixResult->getArray();
  2694.                     } catch (Exception $ex) {
  2695.                         $this->_writeDebug('JAMA Matrix Exception: '.$ex->getMessage());
  2696.                         $result = '#VALUE!';
  2697.                     }
  2698.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is '.self::_showTypeDetails($result));
  2699.                     $stack->push('Value',$result);
  2700.                 } else {
  2701.                     $this->_executeNumericBinaryOperation($cellID,$multiplier,$arg,'*','arrayTimesEquals',$stack);
  2702.                 }
  2703.  
  2704.             } elseif (preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_CELLREF.'$/i', $token, $matches)) {
  2705.                 $cellRef = null;
  2706. //                echo 'Element '.$token.' is a Cell reference<br />';
  2707.                 if (isset($matches[8])) {
  2708. //                    echo 'Reference is a Range of cells<br />';
  2709.                     if (is_null($pCell)) {
  2710. //                        We can't access the range, so return a REF error
  2711.                         $cellValue = PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::REF();
  2712.                     } else {
  2713.                         $cellRef = $matches[6].$matches[7].':'.$matches[9].$matches[10];
  2714.                         if ($matches[2] > '') {
  2715.                             $matches[2] = trim($matches[2],"\"'");
  2716. //                            echo '$cellRef='.$cellRef.' in worksheet '.$matches[2].'<br />';
  2717.                             $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating Cell Range '.$cellRef.' in worksheet '.$matches[2]);
  2718.                             $cellValue = $this->extractCellRange($cellRef, $pCell->getParent()->getParent()->getSheetByName($matches[2]), false);
  2719.                             $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result for cells '.$cellRef.' in worksheet '.$matches[2].' is '.self::_showTypeDetails($cellValue));
  2720.                         } else {
  2721. //                            echo '$cellRef='.$cellRef.' in current worksheet<br />';
  2722.                             $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating Cell Range '.$cellRef.' in current worksheet');
  2723.                             $cellValue = $this->extractCellRange($cellRef, $pCell->getParent(), false);
  2724.                             $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result for cells '.$cellRef.' is '.self::_showTypeDetails($cellValue));
  2725.                         }
  2726.                     }
  2727.                 } else {
  2728. //                    echo 'Reference is a single Cell<br />';
  2729.                     if (is_null($pCell)) {
  2730. //                        We can't access the cell, so return a REF error
  2731.                         $cellValue = PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::REF();
  2732.                     } else {
  2733.                         $cellRef = $matches[6].$matches[7];
  2734.                         if ($matches[2] > '') {
  2735.                             $matches[2] = trim($matches[2],"\"'");
  2736. //                            echo '$cellRef='.$cellRef.' in worksheet '.$matches[2].'<br />';
  2737.                             $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating Cell '.$cellRef.' in worksheet '.$matches[2]);
  2738.                             if ($pCell->getParent()->getParent()->getSheetByName($matches[2])->cellExists($cellRef)) {
  2739.                                 $cellValue = $this->extractCellRange($cellRef, $pCell->getParent()->getParent()->getSheetByName($matches[2]), false);
  2740.                             } else {
  2741.                                 $cellValue = PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::REF();
  2742.                             }
  2743.                             $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result for cell '.$cellRef.' in worksheet '.$matches[2].' is '.self::_showTypeDetails($cellValue));
  2744.                         } else {
  2745. //                            echo '$cellRef='.$cellRef.' in current worksheet<br />';
  2746.                             $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating Cell '.$cellRef.' in current worksheet');
  2747.                             if ($pCell->getParent()->cellExists($cellRef)) {
  2748.                                 $cellValue = $this->extractCellRange($cellRef, $pCell->getParent(), false);
  2749.                             } else {
  2750.                                 $cellValue = NULL;
  2751.                             }
  2752.                             $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result for cell '.$cellRef.' is '.self::_showTypeDetails($cellValue));
  2753.                         }
  2754.                     }
  2755.                 }
  2756.                 $stack->push('Value',$cellValue,$cellRef);
  2757.  
  2758.             // if the token is a function, pop arguments off the stack, hand them to the function, and push the result back on
  2759.             } elseif (preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_FUNCTION.'$/i', $token, $matches)) {
  2760. //                echo 'Token is a function<br />';
  2761.                 $functionName = $matches[1];
  2762.                 $argCount = $stack->pop();
  2763.                 $argCount = $argCount['value'];
  2764.                 if ($functionName != 'MKMATRIX') {
  2765.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating Function '.$functionName.'() with '.(($argCount == 0) ? 'no' : $argCount).' argument'.(($argCount == 1) ? '' : 's'));
  2766.                 }
  2767.                 if ((array_key_exists($functionName, $this->_PHPExcelFunctions)) || (array_key_exists($functionName, $this->_controlFunctions))) {    // function
  2768.                     if (array_key_exists($functionName, $this->_PHPExcelFunctions)) {
  2769.                         $functionCall = $this->_PHPExcelFunctions[$functionName]['functionCall'];
  2770.                         $passByReference = isset($this->_PHPExcelFunctions[$functionName]['passByReference']);
  2771.                         $passCellReference = isset($this->_PHPExcelFunctions[$functionName]['passCellReference']);
  2772.                     } elseif (array_key_exists($functionName, $this->_controlFunctions)) {
  2773.                         $functionCall = $this->_controlFunctions[$functionName]['functionCall'];
  2774.                         $passByReference = isset($this->_controlFunctions[$functionName]['passByReference']);
  2775.                         $passCellReference = isset($this->_controlFunctions[$functionName]['passCellReference']);
  2776.                     }
  2777.                     // get the arguments for this function
  2778. //                    echo 'Function '.$functionName.' expects '.$argCount.' arguments<br />';
  2779.                     $args = $argArrayVals = array();
  2780.                     for ($i = 0; $i < $argCount; ++$i) {

  2890.     private function _validateBinaryOperand($cellID,&$operand,&$stack) {
  2891.         //    Numbers, matrices and booleans can pass straight through, as they're already valid
  2892.         if (is_string($operand)) {
  2893.             //    We only need special validations for the operand if it is a string
  2894.             //    Start by stripping off the quotation marks we use to identify true excel string values internally
  2895.             if ($operand > '' && $operand{0} == '"') { $operand = self::_unwrapResult($operand); }
  2896.             //    If the string is a numeric value, we treat it as a numeric, so no further testing
  2897.             if (!is_numeric($operand)) {
  2898.                 //    If not a numeric, test to see if the value is an Excel error, and so can't be used in normal binary operations
  2899.                 if ($operand > '' && $operand{0} == '#') {
  2900.                     $stack->push('Value', $operand);
  2901.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is '.self::_showTypeDetails($operand));
  2902.                     return false;
  2903.                 } elseif (!PHPExcel_Shared_String::convertToNumberIfFraction($operand)) {
  2904.                     //    If not a numeric or a fraction, then it's a text string, and so can't be used in mathematical binary operations
  2905.                     $stack->push('Value', '#VALUE!');
  2906.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is a '.self::_showTypeDetails('#VALUE!'));
  2907.                     return false;
  2908.                 }
  2909.             }
  2910.         }
  2911.  
  2912.         //    return a true if the value of the operand is one that we can use in normal binary operations
  2913.         return true;
  2914.     }    //    function _validateBinaryOperand()

  2917.     private function _executeBinaryComparisonOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$operation,&$stack,$recursingArrays=false) {
  2918.         //    If we're dealing with matrix operations, we want a matrix result
  2919.         if ((is_array($operand1)) || (is_array($operand2))) {
  2920.             $result = array();
  2921.             if ((is_array($operand1)) && (!is_array($operand2))) {
  2922.                 foreach($operand1 as $x => $operandData) {
  2923.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating '.self::_showValue($operandData).' '.$operation.' '.self::_showValue($operand2));
  2924.                     $this->_executeBinaryComparisonOperation($cellID,$operandData,$operand2,$operation,$stack);
  2925.                     $r = $stack->pop();
  2926.                     $result[$x] = $r['value'];
  2927.                 }
  2928.             } elseif ((!is_array($operand1)) && (is_array($operand2))) {
  2929.                 foreach($operand2 as $x => $operandData) {
  2930.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating '.self::_showValue($operand1).' '.$operation.' '.self::_showValue($operandData));
  2931.                     $this->_executeBinaryComparisonOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operandData,$operation,$stack);
  2932.                     $r = $stack->pop();
  2933.                     $result[$x] = $r['value'];
  2934.                 }
  2935.             } else {
  2936.                 if (!$recursingArrays) { self::_checkMatrixOperands($operand1,$operand2,2); }
  2937.                 foreach($operand1 as $x => $operandData) {
  2938.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating '.self::_showValue($operandData).' '.$operation.' '.self::_showValue($operand2[$x]));
  2939.                     $this->_executeBinaryComparisonOperation($cellID,$operandData,$operand2[$x],$operation,$stack,True);
  2940.                     $r = $stack->pop();
  2941.                     $result[$x] = $r['value'];
  2942.                 }
  2943.             }
  2944.             //    Log the result details
  2945.             $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is '.self::_showTypeDetails($result));
  2946.             //    And push the result onto the stack
  2947.             $stack->push('Array',$result);
  2948.             return true;
  2949.         }
  2950.  
  2951.         //    Simple validate the two operands if they are string values
  2952.         if (is_string($operand1) && $operand1 > '' && $operand1{0} == '"') { $operand1 = self::_unwrapResult($operand1); }
  2953.         if (is_string($operand2) && $operand2 > '' && $operand2{0} == '"') { $operand2 = self::_unwrapResult($operand2); }
  2954.  
  2955.         //    execute the necessary operation
  2956.         switch ($operation) {
  2957.             //    Greater than
  2958.             case '>':
  2959.                 $result = ($operand1 > $operand2);
  2960.                 break;
  2961.             //    Less than
  2962.             case '<':
  2963.                 $result = ($operand1 < $operand2);
  2964.                 break;
  2965.             //    Equality
  2966.             case '=':
  2967.                 $result = ($operand1 == $operand2);
  2968.                 break;
  2969.             //    Greater than or equal
  2970.             case '>=':
  2971.                 $result = ($operand1 >= $operand2);
  2972.                 break;
  2973.             //    Less than or equal
  2974.             case '<=':
  2975.                 $result = ($operand1 <= $operand2);
  2976.                 break;
  2977.             //    Inequality
  2978.             case '<>':
  2979.                 $result = ($operand1 != $operand2);
  2980.                 break;
  2981.         }
  2982.  
  2983.         //    Log the result details
  2984.         $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is '.self::_showTypeDetails($result));
  2985.         //    And push the result onto the stack
  2986.         $stack->push('Value',$result);
  2987.         return true;
  2988.     }    //    function _executeBinaryComparisonOperation()

  2991.     private function _executeNumericBinaryOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$operation,$matrixFunction,&$stack) {
  2992.         //    Validate the two operands
  2993.         if (!$this->_validateBinaryOperand($cellID,$operand1,$stack)) return false;
  2994.         if (!$this->_validateBinaryOperand($cellID,$operand2,$stack)) return false;
  2995.  
  2996.         //    If either of the operands is a matrix, we need to treat them both as matrices
  2997.         //        (converting the other operand to a matrix if need be); then perform the required
  2998.         //        matrix operation
  2999.         if ((is_array($operand1)) || (is_array($operand2))) {
  3000.             //    Ensure that both operands are arrays/matrices
  3001.             self::_checkMatrixOperands($operand1,$operand2,2);
  3002.             try {
  3003.                 //    Convert operand 1 from a PHP array to a matrix
  3004.                 $matrix = new Matrix($operand1);
  3005.                 //    Perform the required operation against the operand 1 matrix, passing in operand 2
  3006.                 $matrixResult = $matrix->$matrixFunction($operand2);
  3007.                 $result = $matrixResult->getArray();
  3008.             } catch (Exception $ex) {
  3009.                 $this->_writeDebug('JAMA Matrix Exception: '.$ex->getMessage());
  3010.                 $result = '#VALUE!';
  3011.             }
  3012.         } else {
  3013.             //    If we're dealing with non-matrix operations, execute the necessary operation
  3014.             switch ($operation) {
  3015.                 //    Addition
  3016.                 case '+':
  3017.                     $result = $operand1+$operand2;
  3018.                     break;
  3019.                 //    Subtraction
  3020.                 case '-':
  3021.                     $result = $operand1-$operand2;
  3022.                     break;
  3023.                 //    Multiplication
  3024.                 case '*':
  3025.                     $result = $operand1*$operand2;
  3026.                     break;
  3027.                 //    Division
  3028.                 case '/':
  3029.                     if ($operand2 == 0) {
  3030.                         //    Trap for Divide by Zero error
  3031.                         $stack->push('Value','#DIV/0!');
  3032.                         $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is '.self::_showTypeDetails('#DIV/0!'));
  3033.                         return false;
  3034.                     } else {
  3035.                         $result = $operand1/$operand2;
  3036.                     }
  3037.                     break;
  3038.                 //    Power
  3039.                 case '^':
  3040.                     $result = pow($operand1,$operand2);
  3041.                     break;
  3042.             }
  3043.         }
  3044.  
  3045.         //    Log the result details
  3046.         $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is '.self::_showTypeDetails($result));
  3047.         //    And push the result onto the stack
  3048.         $stack->push('Value',$result);
  3049.         return true;
  3050.     }    //    function _executeNumericBinaryOperation()

  3078.     public function extractCellRange(&$pRange = 'A1', PHPExcel_Worksheet $pSheet = null, $resetLog=true) {
